    <text id="B2036T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Scott asks how he may receive boxes of books from New York by government post now
                    that the Bureau office in Staunton has closed down.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="Reverend">Rev.</abbr> R. M. <orig
                            reg="Manly">Manley</orig><lb/>Richmond, <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va.</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-12-29"><abbr expan="December">Dec</abbr> 29/68</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, Va.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I write to inquire how boxes are to be directed now so as to come by Government
                    Transportation from the Rooms of the American Missionary Association in <abbr
                        expan="New York">N.Y.</abbr> to me in Staunton Va.</p>

                <p>Heretofore the Bills of <unclear>Leading</unclear> were signed by the <abbr
                        expan="Agent">Agt.</abbr> of the Bureau, but now that there is no Bureau I
                    don't know how to get <del hand="h1">packages</del> boxes of books and clothing.
                    Yet as the Educational Department of the Bureau is to continue I suppose that
                    there a way to get books from <abbr expan="New York">N.Y.</abbr> by <pb n="2"
                    />Government.</p>

                <p>I thought either yourself or <abbr expan="Major">Maj.</abbr> White <abbr
                        expan="Chief Quartermaster">C.Q.M.</abbr>, Bureau <abbr expan="Freedmen">F.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Refugees">R.</abbr> &amp; <abbr expan="Abandoned Lands"
                    >A.L.</abbr> would be able to inform me.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Truly &amp;c</salute>
                    <signed>John Scott</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
